[[File:Pyrefiend icon.png|left]]
'''Pyrefiends''' are [[Slayer monsters]] that require level 30 [[Slayer]] to kill. As their attacks are magic based, it is recommended to wear armour with a high magic defence bonus, such as [[Dragonhide armour|dragonhide]]. Pyrefiends and [[Harpie bug swarms]] are the only monsters to drop [[steel boots]].

While on a pyrefiend slayer task, there is a 1/200 chance that a [[Flaming pyrelord|Flaming Pyrelord]] will spawn after you kill a pyrefiend (if you have [[Slayer Rewards|Bigger and Badder]] unlocked).

==Strength and Weakness==
[[File:Pyrefiend (Fremennik Slayer Dungeon) safespot.png|thumb|220x220px|Players can safespot multiple Pyrefiends by standing in this spot in the Fremennik Slayer Dungeon.]]
The Pyrefiend's attack accuracy is based on the player's magic defence, so it is highly recommended that players wear dragonhides or other ranged armour to mitigate damage. Due to their low magic defence, they are highly susceptible to [[Magic]] attacks.

Players who intend to use melee and have 43 [[Prayer]] can [[Prayer flick|flick]] the [[Protect from Melee]] prayer to avoid being damaged. An alternative method would be to use a safespot with a [[halberd]] or using [[Ranged]] attacks. Players should be aware that although their max hit is relatively low for their combat level, they can hit very consistently. Note that the Dwarf Cannon will not work in Fremennik slayer cave due to the humidity but is functional at the back of the [[Isle of Souls]] in the burnt forest area.

